Initialize a new .common-repo.yaml configuration file

Usage: common-repo init [OPTIONS] [URI]

Arguments:
  [URI]
          Repository URL to initialize from (e.g., https://github.com/org/repo or org/repo)

Options:
  -i, --interactive
          Interactive setup wizard for configuration creation (default when no URI provided)

  -f, --force
          Overwrite existing configuration file

      --color <WHEN>
          Colorize output (always, never, auto)

          [default: auto]

      --log-level <LEVEL>
          Set log level (error, warn, info, debug, trace)

          [default: info]

      --verbose...
          Increase output verbosity (can be repeated: --verbose --verbose)

          Overrides --log-level when specified: --verbose       = debug level --verbose -v    = trace level (combines with command -v flags)

      --quiet
          Suppress output except errors

          Overrides --log-level to show only error messages. Use for scripting or quiet operation.

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
